    "body": "### Problem\n\nI'm using the Arch Linux pacman version of Neovim (v0.10.3-1) using kitty as terminal emulator with hyprland. The issue is as described in the title. Whenever I save the document with :w or quit nvim with :wq the next keyboard action turns off numlock and it has to be reenabled with the numlock button. I'm not using any plugins with neovim. I can't reproduce the issue in vim, though it doesn't happen in tty, so it's likely be connected to wayland or hyprland somehow.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n:w or :wq (with num lock enabled)\npress any other key\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNumlock stays on unless I press numlock.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.10.3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, 9.1.954\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux x86_64, 6.12.6-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.38.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\npacman -S neovim",
